I think that’s a very important observation, with one nuance.

Fear doesn’t always produce overthinking.

But it often recruits overthinking as a socially acceptable disguise.

Instead of saying:

“I’m afraid.”

the mind says:

“I just need a little more information.”

Or:

“One more model.”

“One more spreadsheet.”

“One more book.”

“One more simulation.”

Sometimes that’s wisdom.

Sometimes it’s camouflage.

The difficult part is telling the difference.

